# Trivy Ignore File
#
# Add Trivy finding IDs to suppress known false positives.
# Always include a justification comment.
#
# Format:
#   AVD-AWS-XXXX  # Justification for suppression
#
# Example:
#   AVD-AWS-0089  # S3 bucket logging intentionally disabled for cost savings

# Template placeholder resources — suppress until replaced with real module code
AVD-AWS-0089  # S3 bucket logging not required for template placeholder resource
AVD-AWS-0090  # S3 bucket lifecycle not required for template placeholder resource

# Atom pattern: single-resource modules. Security controls are separate atoms
# composed at the molecule level. Uncomment the lines relevant to your atom:
#
# S3 bucket atoms — public access block is a separate atom
# AVD-AWS-0086  # Public access block is handled by tf-atom-s3-bucket-public-access-block-aws
# AVD-AWS-0087  # Public policy block is handled by tf-atom-s3-bucket-public-access-block-aws
# AVD-AWS-0091  # Ignore public ACLs is handled by tf-atom-s3-bucket-public-access-block-aws
# AVD-AWS-0093  # Restrict public buckets is handled by tf-atom-s3-bucket-public-access-block-aws
# AVD-AWS-0094  # Public access block is handled by tf-atom-s3-bucket-public-access-block-aws
# AVD-AWS-0132  # Customer managed key encryption is handled by tf-atom-s3-bucket-encryption-aws
